Next Post 




            September 28, 2016
        

            Ellyn Shook on Learning from Diversity
        

                
                
                
                By: Accenture Recruitment



Accenture CHRO Ellyn Shook recently co-authored a blog post with Daniella Patrick, product manager at Accenture’s Talent Innovation Lab, highlighting the value of a “What can I learn/What can I teach?” philosophy.  Ellyn’s advice: “Take the time to learn more about each other as individuals instead of putting people in a box.”  
Ellyn explained how we can all learn from embracing diversity, and highlighted the upcoming Hackfest, that Accenture and LinkedIn are sponsoring in Bangalore, India on 24 – 25 September. There, students will innovate solutions that elevate human performance at work.  Check out Ellyn and Daniella’s full post to hear what they each learned from the other, and stay tuned for more information from Ellyn as she attends Hackfest 2016.





Prev. Post


